title: Independent Candidate Sher Ali Arbab wins NA-31 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent Candidate Sher Ali Arbab has won the election for National Assembly constituency NA-31 Peshawar IV by securing 82,985 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Pakistan Peoples Party Parliamentarians Candidate Arbab Alamgir Khan, who bagged 22,543 votes.
Overall votersâ€™ turn-out remained 36.61 percent.
